The function parameter 'daemon' (a pointer parameter) is overwritten by the assignment 'daemon = MHD_get_master(daemon);'. Rule 17.8 forbids modification of a function parameter itself (the pointer variable); only the object it points to may be modified. Overwriting the pointer value therefore violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 17.8. A compliant alternative would be to assign the result to a local variable (e.g. 'struct MHD_Daemon *master = MHD_get_master(daemon);').
